P(A) = 2/3
P(ABC^c) = P(AB) - P(ABC) =  P(AB)-0  = \frac{1}{3}
P(AB^cC) = P(A^cBC) = \frac{1}{3}
\begin{align}P(A) &= P(ABC) + P(ABC^c) + P(AB^cC) + P(AB^cC^c)\\ &= 0 + \frac{1}{3} + \frac{1}{3} + 0\\ &= \frac{2}{3}. \end{align}
P(A \cap B) = P(B \cap C) = P(A \cap C) = \frac{1}{3}
P(A \cap B) + P(B \cap C) + P(A \cap C) = 1
P(A \cap B \cap C) = 0
